ook shows how the intrigue of siblingship renders them an important lens through which to think in new ways about familiar sociological ideas.Siblings and sociology demonstrates why siblings are a fascinating subject for sociologists: a relationship that can influence all aspects of life, as well as an object of scrutiny capable of firing the sociological imagination and directing the analytical gaze.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSiblingsxSocial aspects. 0aSiblingsxSociological aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Marriage & Family.2bisacsh  aAffinities.  aFamily resemblances.  aGeneration.  aMass observation.  aRelationality.  aSibling relationships.  aSiblings.1 aDavies, Katherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packagez978311120645540uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614218440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526142184423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526142184/original  a978-3-11-120645-5  Manchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packageb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles